'''Gabriel Johan Gudmundsson''' (born 29 April 1999) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] for {{English football updater|LeedsUni}} club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==

===Groningen===
On 28 May 2019, it was announced that Gudmundsson had signed for Dutch club [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2286654-fc-groningen-haalt-zweeds-jeugdinternational|title=FC Groningen haalt Zweeds jeugdinternational|date=28 May 2019|website=nos.nl|accessdate=8 July 2025|language=nl}}</ref> The length of his contract was not disclosed,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/fc-groningen-gaat-verder-op-zweedse-toer-en-presenteert-eerste-aanwinst|title=FC Groningen gaat verder op Zweedse toer en presenteert eerste aanwinst|website=Voetbal International|accessdate=8 July 2025|language=nl}}</ref> and the fee was later estimated to be around [[Swedish krona|SEK]] 2.5 million (€250,000).<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=2021-08-31 |title=KLART: Gudmundsson till Lille – dyraste svenska vänsterbacken |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/g6vRMq |access-date=2025-07-08 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |language=sv}}</ref>

===Lille===
On 31 August 2021, Gudmundsson signed a five-year contract with French champions [[Lille OSC|Lille]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Lille OSC|Lille]]|url=https://www.losc.fr/node/107320|title=GABRIEL GUDMUNDSSON, UN ESPOIR SUÉDOIS AU LOSC|date=31 August 2021|language=fr|access-date=16 September 2021|archive-date=31 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831220544/https://www.losc.fr/node/107320|url-status=dead}}</ref> The transfer fee was rumoured by [[Voetbal International]] to be around €6,000,000, though 10% of Groningen's profit went to former club Halmstads BK.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/opluchting-in-groningen-toptransfer-gudmundsson-een-minuut-voor-tijd-rond|title=Opluchting in Groningen: toptransfer Gudmundsson één minuut voor tijd rond|date=31 August 2021|website=vi.nl}}</ref><ref name=":1" />

===Leeds United===
On 8 July 2025, after four seasons with [[Lille OSC|Lille]], Gudmundsson signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/gabriel-gudmundsson-joins-leeds-united |title=Gabriel Gudmundsson joins Leeds United |date=8 July 2025 |publisher=[[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] |access-date=8 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2025-07-08/gabriel-gudmundsson-transfere-leeds-united |title=Gabriel Gudmundsson transféré à Leeds United |date=8 July 2025 |publisher=[[Lille OSC|LOSC]] |access-date=8 July 2025}}</ref> According to various columnists and reporters, the financial details of the transfer include a base fee of €12m (£10.35m).<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |url=https://lepetitlillois.com/2025/07/08/officiel-transfere-en-premier-league-gabriel-gudmundsson-nest-plus-un-joueur-du-losc |title=Officiel : Transféré en Premier League, Gabriel Gudmundsson n'est plus un joueur du LOSC |last=Millot |first=Maxence |date=8 July 2025 |website=Le Petit Lillois |access-date=8 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |language=fr |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Mercato-gabriel-gudmundsson-va-quitter-le-losc-pour-leeds/1576357 |title=Mercato : Gabriel Gudmundsson va quitter le LOSC pour Leeds |last=Gourdol |first=Nathan |date=8 July 2025 |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |access-date=8 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c20rk3m6lpzo |title=Leeds sign Sweden left-back Gudmundsson from Lille |date=8 July 2025 |website=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=8 July 2025}}</ref><ref name="Expressen">{{cite web |language=sv |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/gabriel-gudmundsson-lamnar-lille-klar-for-premier-league |title=Gabriel Gudmundsson lämnar Lille – klar för Premier League |last=Avdic |first=Anel |date=7 July 2025 |newspaper=[[Expressen]] |access-date=7 July 2025}}</ref> His contract includes an annual salary around £3.88m (€4.5m) gross per season.<ref name="Expressen"/>

On 8 March 2026, Gudmundsson recorded his first goal and assist with Leeds United in a 3–0 [[2025–26 FA Cup|FA Cup]] fifth round win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] at [[Elland Road]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gabriel Gudmundsson: We will see what the draw will be - Leeds United |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/gabriel-gudmundsson-we-will-see-what-the-draw-will-be |access-date=2026-03-09 |website=www.leedsunited.com |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
After having represented the [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|Sweden U17]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|U19]], and [[Sweden national under-21 football team|U21]] teams a total of 11 times between 2014 and 2019, Gudmundsson made his full international debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] on 9 June 2022 in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B]] game against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]], replacing [[Viktor Claesson]] in the 77th minute of a 1–0 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sverige – Serbien – Matchfakta – Svensk fotboll |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-serbien-landskamper-herr-senior/5055663/ |access-date=2022-06-10 |website=svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |archive-date=19 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719222851/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-serbien-landskamper-herr-senior/5055663/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Gabriel Gudmundsson – Spelarstatistik – Svensk fotboll |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/gabriel-gudmundsson/6056a965-1dbd-479c-a132-afafb5e375d7/ |access-date=2022-06-10 |website=svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |archive-date=31 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221031185459/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/gabriel-gudmundsson/6056a965-1dbd-479c-a132-afafb5e375d7/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Gudmundsson was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Gabriel is the son of former [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] and [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] player [[Niklas Gudmundsson]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Svensk succédoldis jagas av storklubbar: "Visat vad jag går för"|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/k683jL|access-date=2022-02-01|website=www.aftonbladet.se|language=sv}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Gudmundsson is a [[left-back]] but has also played in [[midfield]] or as a [[centre-back]]. Adam Pope from [[BBC Radio Leeds]] described him as a "good ball-carrier who takes a few risks, and is quick and athletic".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cj3r8xnmmmjo|title=Leeds news: Who is Gabriel Gudmundsson?|date=8 July 2025|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=8 July 2025}}</ref>

